column5: We just crossed the border last week. I was wondering why they ask you how much you paid per case of beer. Is the duty less if you pay more for it or if you pay less for it? Or does it make any difference? thank you.
Obvious, the customs agent wanted to know where to buy his beer.
Expect to pay 6.50 to7.00 dollars duty per case of 24 cans. More you pay for beer the duty goes up, so drink the good stuff MILLER HIGH LIFE !!
Why not buy from the locals and taste real beer.
